articles.author: Kimmy Yam, Alexandra Chaidez
articles.title: Asian Americans see mixed results in enrollment after end of affirmative action - NBC News
articles.description: Asian American enrollment at Columbia and Brown rose following the affirmative action ruling, while it decreased at Yale and Princeton. Harvard remained the same.
articles.content: In the first college admissions process since the Supreme Court struck down affirmative action last year, Asian American enrollment at the most prestigious U.S. schools paints a mixed, uneven picture… [+6831 chars]
